# Daily SOP

## Daily Checklist

```text
[ ] Publish 2 short posts
[ ] Comment or interact with 20 target customers
[ ] Send 5-10 free samples
[ ] Follow up with yesterday's sample users
[ ] Update lead tracker
[ ] Record common questions
[ ] Save good screenshots and testimonials
```

## Morning

1. Review yesterday's leads.
2. Pick the top 5 people to follow up.
3. Publish one pain-point post.
4. Interact with 10 target accounts.

## Afternoon

1. Send free samples to new leads.
2. Ask one qualification question:

```text
Which problem is more urgent right now: traffic, conversion, pricing, or follow-up?
```

3. Send the product page to qualified leads.
4. Log all responses.

## Evening

1. Publish one template/demo post.
2. Follow up with leads who opened or requested samples.
3. Add new objections to the FAQ.
4. Improve one screenshot, sample, or script.

## Weekly Review

Every week, calculate:

- Number of posts
- Number of DMs
- Number of sample requests
- Number of product page visits
- Number of purchases
- Refunds
- Upgrade requests

Then answer:

- Which hook created the most sample requests?
- Which question appeared most often?
- Which niche responded fastest?
- Which tier sold best?
- Which part of the product confused buyers?

